599. latrocinatum, to serve as a mercenary soldier. So in Mil. Glor. 74 the captain calls the men whom he has recruited latrones. The meaning robber is secondapp. The frequent references in come to mercenary soldiers and bragging captains are all from the Greek. The Roman soldiers were still citizens.
